{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Gingerbread cookies","content":["Place butter, golden syrup and sugar into mixing bowl and melt <nobr>2 min\/100°C\/speed 1<\/nobr>. Set aside in mixing bowl to cool (approx. 5 minutes).","Add egg and mix <nobr>5 sec\/speed 4<\/nobr>.","Add remaining biscuit ingredients and mix <nobr>1 min\/speed 3<\/nobr>. Transfer gingerbread dough into a large bowl and cover with plastic wrap. Place dough into refrigerator to chill (approx. 1 hour). Clean and dry mixing bowl.","Preheat oven to 170°C. Line 2 baking trays (30 x 40 cm) with baking paper and set aside.","Divide dough into 3 equal portions. Place 2 portions back into refrigerator. Roll out 1 dough portion between 2 pieces of baking paper and roll out thinly (approx. 5 mm thickness). Dust with extra arrowroot flour as needed to prevent sticking. Remove top layer of baking paper, then cut gingerbread into desired shapes using lightly dusted cookie cutters. Repeat with remaining dough.","Transfer biscuits onto prepared baking trays and bake for 10 minutes (170°C), or until lightly browned at the edges (see Tips).","Allow to cool on trays for 5 minutes, then transfer onto a wire rack to cool completely (approx. 30 minutes)."]},{"title":"Royal icing","content":["Place sugar into mixing bowl and mill <nobr>30 sec\/speed 10<\/nobr>.","Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula. Add egg white and lemon juice and mix <nobr>10 sec\/speed 6<\/nobr> (see Tips).","If icing is too thick, add a few more drops of lemon juice or water and mix <nobr>3 sec\/speed 6<\/nobr>, or until desired consistency is achieved.","Transfer icing into a piping bag with a thin nozzle (5 mm) and decorate gingerbread cookies as desired (see Tips). Leave icing to set (approx. 20 minutes). Transfer into a sealable storage container until ready to serve."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Gingerbread cookies","content":["100 g unsalted butter, cut into pieces","50 g golden syrup","100 g brown sugar","1 egg","60 g gluten free self-raising flour (see Tips)","180 g gluten free flour mix (see Tips)","40 g coconut flour","30 g arrowroot flour, plus extra for dusting","1 tsp gluten free baking powder (see Tips)","3 tsp ground ginger","1 tsp mixed spice"]},{"title":"Royal icing","content":["240 g white sugar","1 egg white","½ tsp lemon juice"]}],"id":"r117984","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-tgB7alJKcdc\/XZWridW4yTI\/AAAAAAAAfos\/Hyq2q5JB4VI3mKKFpuFUSaod8spK2n3dQCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_oKdQJEOMmv4LyppG.png","title":"Gingerbread cookies","publishedAt":"2016-10-16T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"1.29 g","fat":"3.73 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"26.51 g","calories":"597 kJ \/ 142 kcal"},"usefulItems":"rolling pin, large bowl, plastic wrap, 2 baking trays (30 x 40 cm), baking paper, cookie cutter, wire rack, piping bag (thin nozzle), sealable container, refrigerator, oven","hintsAndTricks":["To make your own Gluten free self-raising flour and\/or Gluten free baking powder, please refer to the recipes on this recipe chip.","Please refer to the Gluten free flour mix recipe on this recipe chip.","Baking time will vary slightly depending on the size and shape of your biscuits.","If Royal icing is too thick, add a few more drops of lemon juice or water.","To make coloured icing, distribute icing between several different bowls, then add a few drops of natural food colouring to each bowl."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","2h 35m","24 portions"]}